You are working on Waggle OS, a Tauri 2.0 desktop app (Rust shell) + Vite web app (React 19) + Node.js sidecar.

BEFORE WRITING ANY CODE:
- Read CLAUDE.md at the repo root. It is the authority.
- State your assumptions. If uncertain, ask.
- If multiple approaches exist, present tradeoffs. Don't pick silently.
- Grep before creating. This repo has 16 packages and ~94 files in packages/agent/src alone.

CODE QUALITY:
- Minimum code that solves the problem. Nothing speculative.
- No abstractions for single-use code. No features beyond what was asked.
- Every changed line must trace to the user's request.
- Don't "improve" adjacent code, comments, or formatting.
- Match existing style even if you'd do it differently.
- If you write 200 lines and it could be 50, rewrite it.

VERIFICATION (non-negotiable):
- npx tsc --noEmit --project packages/agent/tsconfig.json
- npx tsc --noEmit --project app/tsconfig.json
- npm run test -- --run

SECURITY (non-negotiable):
- No eval(), no dynamic require()
- All SQL parameterized — no string interpolation
- API keys in .env only, never committed (use packages/core/src/mind/vault.ts)
- scanForInjection() on all external/connector input
- Tauri IPC: scoped capabilities in app/src-tauri/capabilities/, never allowlist all

MONOREPO (16 packages):
- Build order: shared -> core -> agent -> server
- Types from @waggle/shared, memory from @waggle/core, agent logic from @waggle/agent
- Run npm run build:packages after changing any package types
- Two UI trees: app/src/ is Tauri shell (mostly cockpit/), apps/web/src/ is main UI

PATHS THAT MATTER:
- Main web app: apps/web/src/
- Onboarding UI: apps/web/src/components/os/overlays/OnboardingWizard.tsx
- Persona switcher: apps/web/src/components/os/overlays/PersonaSwitcher.tsx
- Personas (data): packages/agent/src/persona-data.ts
- Personas (logic): packages/agent/src/personas.ts
- Tiers: packages/shared/src/tiers.ts (TRIAL/FREE/PRO/TEAMS/ENTERPRISE)
- LLM routing: litellm-config.yaml at root

EXISTING CODE — don't recreate:
- injection-scanner.ts (security scanning)
- cost-tracker.ts (cost/pricing)
- tool-filter.ts (tool filtering)
- kvark-tools.ts (KVARK integration, tier-gated)
- skill-frontmatter.ts (skill parsing)
- feature-flags.ts (feature flags)
- tiers.ts (pricing tiers)
- evolution-*.ts + judge.ts + iterative-optimizer.ts (self-improvement)
- vault.ts (secret storage)

DESIGN SYSTEM:
- Use Hive DS tokens from waggle-theme.css
- Colors: honey #e5a000, hive-950 #08090c, accent #a78bfa
- UI primitives: @base-ui/react + Tailwind 4

TIERS (correct as of April 2026):
- TRIAL $0 / 15 days
- FREE $0 forever
- PRO $19/mo
- TEAMS $49/mo per seat
- ENTERPRISE consultative (KVARK)
Never say "Solo" or "Basic $15" — those names are obsolete.
